[b]MTF WaveTrend Opportunity Hunter[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]

A three-tier multi-timeframe scoring system built around WaveTrend. It evaluates four independent layers — Regime, Opportunity, Timing, and Quality — and fires a signal only when all four layers pass their configured thresholds simultaneously. This structure prevents entries during weak regimes, overextended setups, or low-quality market conditions.

[b]How the layers work[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Regime (35% of final score)[/b] — evaluated on the Regime TF (default: Daily). Scores WT trend direction and momentum, EMA50/200 alignment, ADX strength, and histogram direction. Requires a minimum score before any signal can fire.
[*][b]Opportunity (30% of final score)[/b] — evaluated on the Setup TF (default: 4H). Measures how deeply price has pulled back toward the JMA and how close WaveTrend is to an extreme level. High scores mean price has room to move.
[*][b]Timing (25% of final score)[/b] — evaluated on the Trigger TF (default: 1H). Scores a fresh WT cross, rising WT momentum, and JMA structural alignment. This is the entry trigger layer.
[*][b]Quality (10% of final score)[/b] — evaluated on the Trigger TF. Uses the Efficiency Ratio (directional movement vs. total path), ATR volatility check, optional Relative Strength vs. a benchmark, and JMA acceleration.
[/list]

[b]Visuals[/b]

[list]
[*]LONG / SHORT labels at confirmed signal bars
[*]ATR-based TP1 (1.5×), TP2 (2.5×), TP3 (4.0×) and invalidation (1.2× below/above) lines drawn at each signal
[*]Orange × markers when trend health weakens or WT crosses back against the trade
[*]Optional green/red background tint when the regime score passes the minimum threshold
[*]Dashboard (top-right) showing Final Score, Regime, Opportunity, Timing, Quality, Health, and a Status label
[/list]

[b]Inputs[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Timeframes[/b] — Regime TF, Setup TF, Trigger TF (defaults: D / 240 / 60)
[*][b]WaveTrend[/b] — Channel Length, Average Length, Signal Length, Extreme Level
[*][b]Trend / Regime[/b] — EMA Fast/Slow lengths, ADX Length, Min ADX
[*][b]JMA-like Pullback Smoothing[/b] — Length and Phase for the triple-EMA approximation used on Setup and Trigger TFs
[*][b]Quality[/b] — Efficiency Ratio Length, ATR Length, optional Relative Strength filter with configurable benchmark
[*][b]Signal Thresholds[/b] — independent minimums for each layer plus a minimum Final Score
[*][b]Mode[/b] — Allow Long / Allow Short independently
[*][b]Visuals[/b] — Regime Background, Dashboard, TP/Invalidation Levels
[/list]

[b]Alerts[/b]

[list]
[*]Long signal confirmed
[*]Short signal confirmed
[*]Long trend health weakening
[*]Short trend health weakening
[/list]

